e long.<br><br>this is just a personal opinion, and not a rule being written or anything as i have no power to do so.<br><br>the whole reason (from what i can remember) of the KCoG being formed, was to take ppl to raids there guild wasnt capable off. <br><br>now despite what everyone says, part of the thrill is the chance to role on loot that a lot of people only dream of one day having.<br><br>now then, support groups have been getting bigger, and bigger, and bigger..<br><br>this is great, apart from one thing..<br>im not nameing anyone here but ive had several tells the last few raids from support members and all they have went on about is the loot.<br><br>example (this is taken from a log of mine but ive removed the names)<br><br>x tells you heya i hope i get this damn pally book tonight and not some level 40 pally n00b! ill be so pissed if he does&quot;<br><br>another one<br><br>x tells you &quot;im so sick of waiting for this white scale... whoever gets it im going to hound until they sell me it&quot;<br><br>now im sorry, this spoils the atmosphere for me. many of you who attend cog raids know im always here for support, and ill admit i roled on items at first until i saw the greed in some ppl.<br><br>so what i propose is this..<br><br>only if you engage the dragon u can role on the loot.. tonight we had almosst 3 groups of support, and a few of them needed there epic bits from here. <br><br>you once said killing the dragon was the fun its not about epic bits, if it is your in the wrong place.<br><br>id like to see you stick to that.. dont allow ppl above 53 to role on loot. those that come for support and do it out of the kindness of there own heart it is much appreciated by all the ppl at the raid.<br><br>those that come to get xp killing a few giants then getting to role on the loot, in my eyes is not right.. <br><br>lets keep KCoG for the reason it was created, to help the people who arnt in big guilds kill dragons and have 