ere several people that sent me tells as being ready to walk out of the raid because of statements they made to that effect.  I managed to calm those people down, but morale was definitely affected.  Whatever decisions are made, I know they will be best for the KCoG, and that is what matters for me.  <br><br>I am here for the fun and fellowship, the loot (if I ever get another piece of it) is just possible gravy.  If you come in with that expectation, then you will never be disappointed and you will have much more fun.<br><br>Haemish, thank you for the history and your support!  KCoG would not be the same without your sponsorship and your support, even if it had come to exist in the first place.<br><br>-Farrnusno<br>Guild Leader<br>Souls of the Valiant <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzizzerzazzerzuz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zizzerzazzerzuz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(7/1/02 12:21:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=244.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> my 2 cp</span><hr size=1> anyone wanna hear what i think? no? too bad <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>first of all, one support group w/ 6 higher level people<br><br>cleric (rez's &amp; buffs)<br>tank ( not puller )<br>melle ( puller )<br>shaman ( buffs )<br>druid (  buffs ) <br>rogue ( corpse recovery ) <br><br>lower level bards and chanters are fine for buff lines and higher level chanters/bards are not needed in this group.<br><br>.. i agree they should get to roll on loot ... but more then one support group is not necessary.. why? all the other raiders SHOULD BE INVOLVED in k